CANADIAN PROPERTY CATASTROPHE EXCESS-OF-LOSS REINSURANCE TREATY.

THIS CONTRACT, EFFECTIVE FOR THE PERIOD JULY 1, 2016 THROUGH AND

INCLUDING

JUNE 30, 2017, COVERS THE ACCUMULATION OF NET PROPERTY LOSSES ARISING OUT OF ONE OCCURRENCE ON BUSINESS WRITTEN BY THE COMPANY'S CANADIAN BUSINESSES. THE TREATY COVERS ALL PROPERTY WRITTEN BY

THE COMPANY'S CANADIAN BUSINESSES FOR CANADIAN INSUREDS, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, HABITATIONAL PROPERTY, COMMERCIAL PROPERTY, INLAND MARINE, OCEAN MARINE AND AUTO PHYSICAL DAMAGES EXPOSURES,

WITH RESPECT TO RISKS LOCATED WORLDWIDE, WRITTEN FOR CANADIAN INSUREDS. THE TREATY PROVIDES COVERAGE FOR 50% OF LOSSES IN EXCESS OF C$100 MILLION (US$74 MILLION AT DECEMBER 31,

2016), UP TO C$200 MILLION (US$149 MILLION AT DECEMBER 31, 2016) AND FOR 100% OF LOSSES IN EXCESS OF C$200 MILLION (US$149 MILLION AT DECEMBER 31, 2016), UP

TO C$600 MILLION (US$446 MILLION AT DECEMBER 31, 2016).

