PURPOSES OF THE TABLE, A SIGNIFICANT CATASTROPHE IS AN EVENT FOR WHICH THE COMPANY ESTIMATES ITS ULTIMATE LOSSES WILL BE $100 MILLION OR MORE AFTER REINSURANCE AND BEFORE TAXES.

