$389 MILLION, $14 MILLION OR 3% LOWER THAN IN 2014. THE DECREASE IN 2015 PRIMARILY REFLECTED THE IMPACT OF CERTAIN CUSTOMER-RELATED INTANGIBLE ASSETS BECOMING FULLY AMORTIZED DURING THE

SECOND QUARTER OF 2015.

