$55 MILLION INCREASE IN INCOME BEFORE INCOME TAXES IN 2016. INCOME TAX EXPENSE IN 2015 WAS $272 MILLION, $76 MILLION OR 22% LOWER THAN IN 2014, PRIMARILY REFLECTING THE

$170 MILLION DECREASE IN INCOME BEFORE INCOME TAXES AND THE $16 MILLION REDUCTION IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE IN 2015 RESULTING FROM THE RESOLUTION OF PRIOR YEAR TAX MATTERS.

