1. SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES (CONTINUED)

OR

EVENTS THAT RAISE SUBSTANTIAL DOUBT, MANAGEMENT'S EVALUATION OF THE SIGNIFICANCE OF THOSE CONDITIONS OR EVENTS IN RELATION TO THE ENTITY'S ABILITY TO MEET ITS OBLIGATIONS AND MANAGEMENT'S PLANS

THAT ARE INTENDED TO MITIGATE THOSE CONDITIONS. THE UPDATED GUIDANCE WAS EFFECTIVE FOR ANNUAL PERIODS ENDING AFTER DECEMBER 15, 2016, AND INTERIM AND ANNUAL PERIODS THEREAFTER. THE ADOPTION OF

